SIMPLE: quesal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quesal
<hw>Que*sal"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The long-tailed, or resplendent, trogon (<spn>Pharomachus
mocinno</spn>, formerly <spn>Trogon resplendens</spn>), native of
Southern Mexico and Central America. Called also
<altname>quetzal</altname>, and <altname>golden
trogon</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The male is remarkable for the brilliant metallic green
and gold colors of his plumage, and for his extremely long plumes, which
often exceed three feet in length.</note><-- The feathers were valued as
part of the dress of Inca kings. Now usu. called quetzal. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1177 --></p>

<p><ent>Quest</ent>⟦br⟧
